body:
The following test fails currently on master:
```systemverilog
module t (input wire clk);
   wire a;
   assign a = clk;

   always begin
      if (a === 1'bz)
         $stop;

      if (a === clk) begin
         $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
         $finish;
      end
   end

endmodule
```
The problem is that comparison `a === 1'bz` returns true. If we replace reference to input port with constant, it works then properly.
